The paper deals with communication complexity lower bounds for finding correlated equilibria in two-player games, which is a topic that falls under computational complexity (cs.CC) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also uses techniques from data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT) to prove the lower bound. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of randomized algorithms and approximation algorithms, which are topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
